The paper is about relevance judgment in Information Retrieval, which is a core topic in the field of Information Retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the methodology to construct incompatible basis for documents from real-world query log data, which involves data processing and analysis, making cs.QL (Query Languages and Information Retrieval) another likely sub-category. The paper also uses Bell-type inequalities to test the quantum nature of relevance judgments, which involves mathematical modeling and analysis, making cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper also discusses the various factors that influence relevance judgments, which involves a multidimensional perspective, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible sub-category as well.
